Trust the Development Certificate
If you’re using HTTPS locally, ensure the development certificate is trusted.

Trust the Certificate
Run the following command to trust the development certificate:

cmd
Copy
dotnet dev-certs https --trust
Restart your computer if prompted.

Verify the Certificate
Open the Certificate Manager:

Press Win + R, type certmgr.msc, and press Enter.

Navigate to:

Copy
Personal > Certificates
Look for a certificate issued to localhost and ensure it’s valid.
